{
  "stem": "9701.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And Beatrice Mayer had contacted Rabbi Amias, A-M-I-A-S, who in turn found the family that I stayed with.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the family was-- name was-- the husband's name was Sydney Rose, R-O-S-E.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They lived in Edgeware, E-D-G-E-W-A-R-E, which is sort of a suburb of London.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had three children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "One of them-- three daughters, one was older than I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the middle child was the same age as I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then, there was a younger one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I arrived in England on the 19th of May, 1939.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I just recently attended a conference, a children's transport conference.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Maybe later on, I can talk a little bit about that, because that's where I learned some of how this all came about.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Two or three days after I arrived in England, I started school in Edgeware Senior High School.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I had absolutely no idea what was going on at school because my English was so limited, and the Rose family spoke no German.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so I was forced to learn English because how else was I going to communicate.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I stayed in written contact with my parents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We-- I received letters from them almost daily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I wrote almost daily to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Life at the Rose family was not easy for me, but I never shared that with my parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was told, or was given to understand, and I understood it in more ways than one very quickly, that when I lived in Germany, I was starving, which was really not true.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because the only thing that I remember is that butter was rationed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And you certainly can live well and eat well without ever touching butter.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
